               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1700" notAfter="1799">18th
                                cent.</origDate>
                     <origPlace> Ethiopia.</origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  
                  <provenance> The manuscript was purchased by William Simpson, an
                            illustrator for the Illustrated London News and member of the <date>1868</date>
                            Napier expedition to <origPlace>Magdala</origPlace>. According to a
                            note on the <locus from="i" to="i">inside front cover</locus>, William Simpson, ,
                            whose monogram is also included, obtained it from an Ethiopian as the
                            troops returned to Aden after the defeat of Tewodros II: “This book of
                            Devotion, 350 or 400, years old, I bought from an Abyssinnian [sic], at
                            the tent door, during the return march from <origPlace>Magdala</origPlace>, <date>1868</date>”. The seller
                            may have been either Waldä Giyorgis or
                                Śarḍa Māryām, both of whose names
                            appear in the manuscript.</provenance>
               </history>
